net.dempsy.serialization.kryo

Class KryoSerializer

  • java.lang.Object
    • net.dempsy.serialization.Serializer
      • net.dempsy.serialization.kryo.KryoSerializer

  • public class KryoSerializer
extends Serializer
    This is the implementation of the Kryo based serialization for Dempsy. It can be configured with registered classes using Spring by passing a list of Registration instances to the constructor.

    • Constructor Detail

      • KryoSerializer

        public KryoSerializer()

      • KryoSerializer

        public KryoSerializer(boolean manageExactClasses)
        Create an unconfigured default KryoSerializer with no registered classes. If you set manageExactClasses then the result of serializing and then deserializing a class by referring to its superclass will result in the original class. Otherwise the class passed to the deserialize call will be the actual class that's deserialized.

      • KryoSerializer

        public KryoSerializer(boolean manageExactClasses,
                      Registration... regs)
        Create an KryoSerializer with the provided registrations. This can be used from a Spring configuration.
